<paragraph id="0703185BFF98FF8FB994FB260B4FF94A" blockId="19.[163,779,1544,1719]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF98FF8FB994FB260B0BF9E0" box="[163,605,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF98FF8FB875FB260B0BF9E0" box="[322,605,1544,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yavapai">Caenocentron yavapai</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF98FF8FB994FB09080DF9C6" authorityName="Vilarino &amp; Dias &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[163,347,1574,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafamoralesi">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF98FF8FB994FB09080DF9C6" box="[163,347,1574,1596]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">C. rafamoralesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the apical projection of sternum IX. It is distinguished by the trifid apical projection of coxopodite; dorsal margin of sternum IX not prominent, and the broad elongated apex of sternum IX with a pair of short processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0703185BFF98FF8FB994FBCE0D1DFA0E" blockId="19.[163,778,1757,1904]" lastBlockId="19.[827,1443,1378,1523]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF98FF8FB994FBCE09A6F908" box="[163,240,1760,1781]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">Adult:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="B7D41206FF98FF8FB9C8FBCE0D11FA0E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3751569311" collectionCode="IV, II, V" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" specimenCode="R1" specimenCount="2" specimenCount-male="2">
Forewing length 4.0 mm (
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF98FF8FBB7EFBCE0B0BF908" box="[585,605,1760,1781]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">N</emphasis>
= 
<specimenCount id="11BAD3D2FF98FF8FBB4AFBCE0BCAF908" box="[637,668,1757,1781]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" type="male">2♂</specimenCount>
). Colour (in alcohol) uniformly dark brown. Maxillary palp formula (I-II-III)-IV-V; segment 
<collectionCode id="61AD809EFF98FF8FBB2DFA300B60F8CE" box="[538,566,1822,1843]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">IV</collectionCode>
shorter than sum of segments I-II-III; tibial spurs 2-4- 
<quantity id="C044B5BEFF98FF8FBB7CFA120B21F8AF" box="[587,631,1852,1874]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
males, 2-4- 
<quantity id="C044B5BEFF98FF8FBBCBFA1209EDF88D" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
females, male hindleg apical spur unmodified. Venation: forewing fork 
<collectionCode id="61AD809EFF98FF8FBD47F84D0DD3FA85" box="[1136,1157,1379,1400]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">II</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="61AD809EFF98FF8FBDFEF84D0DB0FA85" box="[1225,1254,1379,1400]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">IV</collectionCode>
present, three anal veins present; hindwing fork 
<collectionCode id="61AD809EFF98FF8FBDE0F8AF0DBAFA6B" box="[1239,1260,1409,1430]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">II</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="61AD809EFF98FF8FBC1EF8AF0C6DFA6B" box="[1321,1339,1409,1430]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
present, transverse vein between 
<specimenCode id="571AB020FF98FF8FBD78F88E0D39FA48" box="[1103,1135,1440,1461]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360">R1</specimenCode>
and SR present.Abdominal sternum 
<collectionCode id="61AD809EFF98FF8FBA95F8910AE2FA29" box="[930,948,1471,1492]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="19" pageNumber="1360" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
with anterolateral oval region with cuticle modified and reticulate
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
